$ Oracle: Optimizer statistics advisor

*Optimizer statistics advisor* is a built-in diagnostic tool that allows to manage → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer/statistics[statistics].

The goal of this advisor is
  • Reviewing the process of gathering statistics
  • Validation of the quality of existing statistics
  • Checking the status of *auto stats gathering*

The statistics advisor checks a set of rules against the data found in the → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary. Rules that are violated (or «broken») result in
a *findings* and *recommendations*.
-
The recommendations can then be turned into *actions* (for example an SQL script) which fix the broken rules.

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/stats_advisor/rules[`v$stats_advisor_rules`]
